The paper introduces a new method for constructing normalizing flows, which are a type of deep generative model used in machine learning. The paper focuses on the efficiency of the method, which allows for high-dimensional interactions, efficient sampling, and efficient likelihood evaluation. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT).
